  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1 id='description'><title>Description</title>
  <para>
    <command>lwmastermon</command><manvolnum>1</manvolnum>
    is a GUI applet that displays the IP address of the current master node
    on a LiveWire network. It does so by subscribing to the multicast address
    239.192.255.2 (the address for LiveWire clock packets) and listening
    for traffic on UDP port 7000.  If no clock traffic is heard for more
    than two seconds, a warning message is displayed.
  </para>
  </refsect1>

